    "### Channel-wise Statistics\n",
    "\n",
    "Summary stats (min, max, mean, active %) for each of the 8 sub-detector channels. The data is extremely sparse \u2014 most channels have fewer than 2% active pixels per image.\n"
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": "sample0 = data\nprint(f\"Jet shape: {data.shape}\")\nprint(f\"Value range: min = {data.min():.1f} , max = {data.max():.1f}\")\n\n\n# Channel mapping based on CMS detector layout\nCHANNEL_NAMES = [\n    'Ch0: BPIX Layer 1 (inner pixel)',\n    'Ch1: BPIX Layer 2 (middle pixel)',\n    'Ch2: BPIX Layer 3 (outer pixel)',\n    'Ch3: Reconstructed Tracks (pT)',\n    'Ch4: ECAL (electromagnetic)',\n    'Ch5: HCAL (hadronic)',\n    'Ch6: TIB/TOB (strip tracker)',\n    'Ch7: TEC/TID (strip endcap)',\n]\n\nprint(f'{\"Channel\":<40} {\"Min\":>6} {\"Max\":>6} {\"Mean\":>10} {\"Nonzero\":>10} {\"Active%\":>8}')\nprint('-' * 85)\nfor ch in range(8):\n    vals = data[..., ch]\n    nz = (vals > 0).sum()\n    denom = vals.size \n    print(f'{CHANNEL_NAMES[ch]:<40} {vals.min():>6.0f} {vals.max():>6.0f} '\n          f'{vals.mean():>10.4f} {nz:>10} {100*nz/denom:>7.1f}%')",
