   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "### Spatial Footprint: Quark vs Gluon\n",
    "\n",
    "Active pixel count per jet (summed across all channels). Gluon jets are broader \u2014 gluons carry higher color charge ($C_A = 3$ vs $C_F = 4/3$), radiating more particles into wider showers. The distributions overlap heavily, so pixel count alone can't separate the classes.\n"
   ],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": "quark_samples = data[label == 0]\ngluon_samples = data[label == 1]\nquark_active = np.array([(s.sum(axis=-1) > 0).sum() for s in quark_samples])\ngluon_active = np.array([(s.sum(axis=-1) > 0).sum() for s in gluon_samples])\n\nfig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))\nax.hist(quark_active, bins=40, alpha=0.6, color='#2196F3', label=f'Quark (mean={quark_active.mean():.0f})', edgecolor='black')\nax.hist(gluon_active, bins=40, alpha=0.6, color='#FF5722', label=f'Gluon (mean={gluon_active.mean():.0f})', edgecolor='black')\nax.set_xlabel('Number of Active Pixels')\nax.set_ylabel('Count')\nax.set_title('Active Pixel Count Distribution: Quark vs Gluon')\nax.legend(fontsize=11)\nax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig('eda_quark_vs_gluon_active_pixels.jpg', dpi=150)\nplt.show()\n\nprint(f'Quark: mean={quark_active.mean():.0f}, median={np.median(quark_active):.0f}')\nprint(f'Gluon: mean={gluon_active.mean():.0f}, median={np.median(gluon_active):.0f}')",
